         <abstract>
            <p>A computable error bound for mixed finite element methods is established in the model case of the Poisson-problem to control the error in the &lt;tex-math&gt;$H(\operatorname{div}, \Omega) \times L^2(\Omega)$&lt;/tex-math&gt;-norm. The reliable and efficient a posteriori error estimate applies, e.g., to Raviart-Thomas, Brezzi-Douglas-Marini, and Brezzi-Douglas-Fortin-Marini elements.</p>
          </abstract>
